strapiSongs.title: The Cult of Unknown
strapiSongs.lyrics:
We lived to see the darkness
They claimed it was long left behind
The power was too intoxicating
To withstand and behold by the blind

We had to hold together
But there were far too few to be found
For the wisdom was long forgotten
To a fate we denied we were bound
strapiSongs.credits:
Music by Victor Fisher

Started Writing: 10/8/21
Recording Day 1: 4/29/22 - Main Instruments and Vocals
Recording Day 2: 4/30/22 - Drums and Bass
Recording Day 3: 5/1/22 - Final Touches to Drums and Mix, Deployment
strapiSongs.description:
This song reflects upon the extradordinary nature of our current place in history.

It features acoustic guitar and violin.
